// Cipr Standard Prelude
// Auto-injected into every compilation unit.
// Intentionally minimal — only what every program unconditionally needs.
// All other standard library features require an explicit include.
//
// Built-in functions (no declaration needed, handled by the compiler):
//   print(x)  — works for int, float, bool, str
//   new T(...)  — heap allocation
//   delete ptr  — heap deallocation
